02/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Friday (28 February), President Boris Trajkovski met for the first time with Democratic Union of Integration leader Ali Ahmeti. 
Party spokeswoman Ermira Mehmeti said they agreed on the formation of an ethnically mixed antiterrorism unit, to build mutual confidence and contribute to a joint fight against organised crime and related activities. 
They also discussed the current security and political situation and the implantation of Ohrid peace accord. 
Ahmeti meanwhile, plans to travel to Kosovo on Tuesday, to meet with President Ibrahim Rugova and UNMIK chief Michael Steiner. 
(A1 TV - 01/03/03; A1 TV - 28/02/03)
